.\" playfield-bcc.1.mdoc - Playfield bytecode compiler manpage
.Dd January 2026
.Dt PLAYFIELD-BCC 1
.Os Playfield Engine 1.0
.Sh NAME
.Nm playfield-bcc
.Nd compile Ray scripts into bytecode files
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar sourcefiles ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
translates Ray script files
.Pa .ray
into bytecode files with the extension
.Pa .raybc .
.Pp
Each input file is compiled independently.
The output file has the same basename as the input,
with its extension replaced by
.Pa .raybc .
For example, compiling
.Pa sample.ray
produces
.Pa sample.raybc
in the same directory.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Compile a single script:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
playfield-bcc main.ray
.Ed
.Pp
Compile multiple scripts:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
playfield-bcc main.ray enemy.ray level.ray
.Ed
.Pp
The above command produces:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
main.raybc enemy.raybc level.raybc
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr playfield (1) ,
.Xr playfield-aotc (1),
.Xr playfield-pack (1)
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Awe Morris Aq Mt awe@noctvm.io
and contributors.
Project homepage:
.Lk https://github.com/awemorris/PlayfieldEngine
